  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0da7 12,444 \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "12,444 per month to tie the knot",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the latest reports of the Department of Population and Statistics, a minimum amount of 12444 rupees was enough for one person to live for a month in Sri Lanka by meeting basic needs.",
        "According to the report, a minimum amount of 13,421 rupees was required to meet the basic needs of last June in Colombo district and it is the highest amount needed for a month of living in a district of Sri Lanka.",
        "According to the report issued by the Department of Population and Statistics, last June in Monaragala district, an amount of 11899 rupees was required to live for a month by meeting the basic needs and that is the lowest amount required to live for a month by meeting the basic needs of a district in Sri Lanka."
      ],
